original_properties.Shop: Campo Green Store is a small store in Campo, 2/10 mile E of PCT on Hwy 94.
Oak Shores Malt Shop small hiker-friendly convenience store with a cafe/deli, and ATM. 4/10 mile SE of PCT in Lake Morena Village.
Mount Laguna has a lodge  with a store, restaurant, ATM, and nearby Post Office  4/10 mile W of PCT.
Julian is a small hiker-friendly town with restaurants, motels, small grocery store, good outfitter, Post Office.
The small Montezuma Valley Market is 4 miles E of the PCT on Montezuma Valley Road.
Warner Springs is a very small community with a hiker-friendly community resource center, hot spring resort, golf course, restaurant, gas station mini-mart, Post Office
Paradise Valley Cafe with good hamburgers and water spigot outside.
Idyllwild is a hiker-friendly town with restaurants, motels, a state park campground w/ showers, grocery store, natural food store, pharmacy, good outfitter, Post Office, laundry, ATM, and library.
Cabazon is a small community with a small store, ATM, and Post Office .
Big Bear Lake is a large town with restaurants, motels, the hiker-friendly Big Bear Hostel, large grocery stores, Dollar Tree, pharmacy, Post Office, hospital, ATMs, and bus service
Interstate Highway 15 at Cajon Pass is a busy interstate highway intersection with a McDonald's restaurant, hiker-friendly Cajon Pass Inn, and Chevron gas station with mini-mart, ATM.
Wrightwood is a small hiker-friendly town with restaurants, motels, large grocery store, hiker-friendly hardware store, Post Office, ATMs, and library.
Los Angeles RV Resort with camping [$15/person], showers, laundry, small store, Uber/ride share, accepts resupply packages [$5].
Agua Dulce is a small town on the PCT with restaurants, and ATM.
Hikertown is an odd assortment of cottages resembling a western movie set turned into a hiker hostel on the PCT at Hwy 138.
Tehachapi is a town with restaurants, motels, large grocery stores, Walmart, several Dollar stores, pharmacy, Post Office, library, hospital, laundry, ATMs, and Kerntransit.org bus service.
Onyx is a very small community with a post office, and the historic Onyx store  with snacks, sandwiches, drinks, no overnight stays, and bus service.
Kennedy Meadows South is a small hiker-friendly community with a small general store, restaurant, and outfitter.
Lone Pine is a small town with a restaurants, motels, grocery store, outfitter, pharmacy, Post Office, hospital, laundry, ATMs, and bus service.
Independence is a small town with restaurants, motels, gas station mini-mart, ATM, Post Office, and bus.
Muir Trail Ranch is a private guest ranch that accepts hiker resupply packages and sells a few emergency supplies. 1.5 miles NW of PCT on the Florence Lake Trail.
Vermilion Valley Resort is a hiker-friendly resort with a small store, restaurant, tent cabins, showers, and laundry.
Red's Meadow is a pack station with lodging, good restaurant, a small store offering limited resupply, laundry, nearby campground with hot spring showers.
Mammoth Mountain Ski Lodge, 4.2 miles SE of PCT on Minaret Summit Road.
Tuolumne Meadows has a snack bar, surprisingly well stocked camp store, Post Office, campground with backpacker campsites and bus service.
Kennedy Meadows North is a pack station and resort with restaurant, lodging, small store, pay phone, laundry, showers, WiFi, and nearby Forest Service campground.
South Lake Tahoe is a large town with restaurants, motels, large grocery stores, pharmacy, Post Office, hospital, ATMs, and Uber/ride share.
Echo Chalet store and deli on Echo Lake is a small resort with a deli, small store with limited resupply, cabins.
Soda Springs is a community with a restaurant, store, ATM, and Post Office.
Sierra City is a small town with restaurants, motels, small store, ATM, Post Office, and a library.
Haskins Inn & Store is a small convenience store, sandwich shop, next to a bed and breakfast.
Quincy is a town with restaurants, motels, grocery stores, natural food store, pharmacy, Post Office, hospital, laundry, ATMs, and bus service.
Belden is a small resort and lodge on the PCT with a restaurant, bar, very small store, ATM, and cabin rentals.
Chester is a town with restaurants, motels, large grocery store, pharmacy, Post Office, hospital , laundry, showers, ATMs, and bus service.
Drakesbad Guest Ranch is a hiker-friendly hot spring resort on the PCT in Lassen National Park with and excellent restaurant, cabins, and they accept resupply packages.
Old Station is a very small community with a mini-mart, RV park/resort, Post Office.
JJ's Cafe is open Su-Th 7-3, Fr-Sa 7-7:30, 1/2 mile SW of Hwy 44.
Burney is a small town with restaurants, motels, grocery stores, pharmacy, Post Office, laundry, ATMs.
Burney Falls State Park is along the PCT with a campground, coin showers, and a small store that accepts hiker resupply packages.
Castella is a very small community and nearby state park, with the Ammirati Market, state park campground, coin showers, and a Post Office.
Etna is a small hiker-friendly town with restaurants, motels, grocery, Etna Creek Outfitters, Dollar General, library, Post Office, laundry, ATMs.
Seiad Valley is a very small hiker-friendly community on the PCT with a cafe, small store, Post Office, WiFi, and Mid River RV Park w/ hiker camping, laundry, showers.
Ashland is a large town with restaurants, motels, large grocery stores, food co-op, Dollar Tree, pharmacy, outfitter,Post office, laundry, hospital, showers, ATMs, and bus service.
Green Springs Inn is a small resort with lodging and a restaurant.
Campers Cove/Hyatt Lake Resort with rental cabins, restaurant and a very small store.
Fish Lake Resort  is a hiker-friendly resort that has a cafe, campground, cabins, laundry, showers, very small store and they accept resupply packages.
Mazama Village has a restaurant, lodge, and campground with a small store, cabins, WiFi, laundry, showers.
Shelter Cove Resort is a hiker friendly resort and RV park with hiker camping, cabins, remodeled kitchen serving good food, small but decent resupply store, showers, laundry, and WiFi.
Willamette Ski Resort has a pizza restaurant that is sometimes open on summer weekends.
Elk Lake Resort, friendly helpful staff, excellent restaurant food, showers, no public laundry, small store only sells a few snacks.
Sisters is a small town with restaurants, motels, campground, grocery stores, pharmacy, Post Office and ATMs.
Big Lake Youth Camp is a hiker-friendly Seventh-day Adventist church camp. They offer, showers, WiFi, laundry, meals, and they accept resupply packages. Camping available on nearby forest land.
Olallie Lake Resort is a small hiker-friendly resort with small store, cabins, yurts, boat rental, and campground.
Highway 26, Wapinitia Pass Trailhead parking, outhouse, trash cans nearby. CJ's Foodmart and Chevron is 1.9 miles NW of the PCT on Hwy 26.
Timberline Lodge is a historic ski resort, restaurant, and lodge that accepts hiker resupply packages.
Cascade Locks is a small town on the PCT with restaurants, motels, campgrounds, showers, grocery store, ATMs, daily ridecatbus.org bus service to Portland & Hood River, and a Post Office.
Trout Lake is a small town that has a restaurant, lodging, small grocery store, ATM, and Post Office.
White Pass is a small ski area with a motel and the Kracker Barrel convenience store with deli, laundry, showers, WiFi, and they accept hiker resupply packages.

Snoqualmie Pass is a busy Interstate Highway 90 intersection and small ski area, on the PCT. Snoqualmie pass has restaurants, the Summit Inn that accepts resupply packages, Chevron station  with a market, ATMs, and the small Lee Grocery.
Skykomish is a small community with restaurants, motel, Post Office, laundry, small store, and ATM.

Stehekin is a small community with bakery, lodge, Post Office, ferry service. Seasonal shuttle bus service connects the PCT at High Bridge with Stehekin. No cell service, a community satellite pay phone is located near the boat dock.
Mazama is a small town with restaurants, motels, a good store, an outfitter that accepts hiker resupply packages, and trail angel Ravensong.
Highway 3, near the Manning Park Lodge. The Manning Park offers a restaurant, lodging, small store, and ATM.
